author: Staff writers
title: First Aussie review of UK Bunnings’ snags
text:
AFTER Bunnings opened its first store in the UK, this Aussie went to see if its most iconic product — the Bunnings sausage — was up to scratch. 
After sampling the sausage — served in the traditional way outside the new store in St Albans, Hertfordshire, Sam Ashleigh said the “wonderfully juicy” snack did us proud.
“I think it’s worthy of the Bunnings name,” she concluded.
“(It has) nice smoky barbecue flavour.”
The new store last week f lung open its doors, with Wesfarmers looking to take on British rival Kingfisher. 
Whether or not the Brits will take up the sausage sizzle is yet to be seen.
Bunnings Warehouse opened their first UK store in St Albans Hertfordshire. Picture: Mega Source: news.com.au 
Originally published as First Aussie review of UK Bunnings’ snags
